# Helping Youtube Vedio: https://youtu.be/APOPm01BVrk

# keep a project a n directory. for example we will use Desktop

# Go to the directory where project exit: cd Desktop

# Create project folder: mkdir my_project

# Create Environment on that folder: python -m venv my_project\(userdefined name of environment. here venv)

# Activate that environment: my_project\venv\Scripts\activate.bat

# How to install packages and libraries exist in requirement.txt file: pip install -r requirements.txt

# check installation: pip list

# Enter into project folder: cd my_project

# Deactivate Environment: deactivate

# Delete Environment: rmdir venv /s
